13.44	Friedrich_Froebel	Friedrich Fröbel	Friedrich Wilhelm August Fröbel (or Froebel) (German pronunciation: ; April 21, 1782 – June 21, 1852) was a German pedagogue, a student of Pestalozzi who laid the foundation for modern education based on the recognition that children have unique needs and capabilities. He developed the concept of the “kindergarten”, developed the Froebel Gifts educational toys, and also coined the word now used in German and English.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/82/Frederick-Froebel-Bardeen.jpeg/200px-Frederick-Froebel-Bardeen.jpeg
